We recommended that Management:
1. Direct the City Accountant to review the individual accounts of JOs to come up with data such as how much were actually deducted and remitted;
2. To reconcile the payments recorded by the accounting against the remittances received by the SSS;
3. To consult JOs if they are amenable to apply their unremitted premiums to pay for their monthly contributions in advance since self-employed and voluntary members may pay their monthly contributions prospectively or in advance, but never retroactively to cover months when no contribution payments were remitted.
4. To remit in full the amount due to SSS within the prescribed period to ensure that JO may enjoy the full benefits from SSS. Otherwise, appropriate penal sanctions may be imposed upon city officials for violating pertinent provisions of the SSS Law.
